On May 11, 2009, Press Secretary Robert Gibbs released a statement from the White House regarding General McKiernan. The statement mentioned that President Obama agreed with the Secretary of Defense and Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff that a new strategy in Afghanistan required new military leadership. However, the President expressed gratitude and admiration for General McKiernan's leadership and his efforts in requesting additional resources for the fight in Afghanistan. The statement emphasized that the change in leadership did not diminish the President's respect for General McKiernan's decades of public service.